T1  - Demand for India's manufactured exports
AU  - Lucas, Robert E.B.
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 29
IS  - 1
SP  - 63
EP  - 75
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/07/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(88)90071-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387888900715
AB  - Surprisingly few estimates exist of disaggregated world demand functions for LDC exports, despite the obvious policy importance of the inherent price elasticities. Time-series, simultaneous equation estimates are herein presented of world demand for 23 categories of manufactured exports from India. Tests for homotheticity, separability, whether price elasticity of demand differs during world recession, and for effects of foreign learning about India's exports are reported. Estimated price elasticities range from below unity to infinity, revealing important variations masked by aggregate studies. These results raise considerable doubts about policy design from a uniform small country assumption.
