UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387888900703
AB  - This paper utilizes a unique data set to develop a methodology to estimate the intrinsic land quality for farm households in India. In contrast to earlier attempts, this land quality is estimated, not at the regional level, but at an individual farm level. The results suggest that the distribution of (effective) land in India is much more equal than conventionally assumed. For example, though the bottom 40% of farm households have only 7% of nominal land, it is likely that they have almost 20% of quality adjusted land.
